Vice President Mike Pence met with Colombian Vice President Oscar Naranjo to discuss the partnership between the United States and Colombia. They addressed issues such as the fight against illegal drugs, implementation of the Colombian Peace Accords, and opportunities for economic growth. Pence praised Colombia's counternarcotics efforts but stressed the need for more effective eradication techniques. They also discussed ways to enhance interdiction operations to stop drug shipments to the US. Pence expressed support for Colombia's ambition to join the OECD, urging progress on labor and trade concerns. The leaders also expressed concern for the crisis in Venezuela and their commitment to supporting the restoration of democracy in the country.